==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg-y|autonom|y}}

# Self-[[government]].
# ''(moral, political, and bioethical philosophy)'' The capacity of a rational individual to make an informed, uncoerced decision.  In moral and political philosophy, autonomy is often used as the basis for determining moral responsibility for one's actions.  In medicine, respect for the autonomy of patients is considered obligatory for doctors and other healthcare professionals.

